<%= stylesheet 'info', :media => :all %>
<%= javascript 'info' %>
  <div id="maincontent">
    <div id="vod-wrap">
      <div class="top"></div>
      <div id="main_box">
        <div id="top_box">
          <h1 title="How to watch streamed movies on your TV">okHow to connect your PC <br />
            to <font color="#FF3300">your TV</font></h1>
          <p id="intro_copy"> Most TVs come with suitable "connectors", enabling you to hook up your laptop or computer to your TV. All you need is a cable; and stick one end in your laptop or computer, and the other end in your TV.<br>
            It's easier than you think. </p>
          <div id="left_box">
            <p>Just answer the <strong>2 questions below</strong> and we will help you find which cable you need.</p>
            <h3>1. Check the connector on your computer</h3>
            <p>Look on the sides, back or front of your computer and click the matching connector below.</p>
            <h3>2. Check the connector on your TV</h3>
            <p>Look on the sides or back of your TV and click the matching connector below.</p>
          </div>
          <div id="right_box">
            <p>As soon as you've bought the cable suggested and connected your computer, you should be able to <%= link_to 'stream our films', products_path(:view_mode => :streaming) %>, and enjoy them on your TV.</p>
            <p>This service is available to all users of DVDPost. For those on an Unlimited package, there are thousands of titles at no extra cost. Premium titles are available to everyone on pay-per-view basis, and a number of titles are available to all site visitors for free with advertising support.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p id="enjoy">Give it a go and enjoy <%= link_to 'streamed movies', products_path(:view_mode => :streaming) %> on your TV.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="clearfix"></div>
        </div>
        <div id="guide_smallprint">
          <p>We hope that each and every cable suggested works perfectly. But if you do encounter any problems, please check the operating instructions of your laptop/computer and TV, or contact the manufacturers for further help.</p>
        </div>
        <div id="middle_box">
          <div class="options_box" id="box_output">
            <h2>Step 1</h2>
            <div class="options_top">
              <h3>Check the connector <br />
                on <font color="#FF3300">your computer</font></h3>
              <%= image_tag 'your_comp.jpg' %>
              <p>Select a matching connector</p>
            </div>
            <%= render :partial => "info/get_connected/step1" %>
          </div>
          <div class="options_box" id="box_input">
            <h2>Step 2</h2>
            <div class="options_top">
              <h3>Check the connector<br />
                on <font color="#FF3300">your TV</font></h3>
              <img src="/images/your_tv.jpg" alt="Check the connector on your TV">
              <p>Select a matching connector</p>
            </div>
            <%= render :partial => "info/get_connected/step2" %>
          </div>
          <div class="options_box" id="option_last">
            <h2>Step 3</h2>
            <div class="options_top">
              <h3>Here's what <br />
                <font color="#FF3300">we suggest</font></h3>
              <img src="/images/suggested.jpg" alt="Suggested connection">
              <p style="display: block;">Please complete steps 1 and 2</p>
            </div>
            <%= render :partial => "info/get_connected/step3" %>
          <div class="clearfix"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="end"></div>
  </div>
  <div style='display:none'>
    <div id='locale'><%= I18n.locale %></div>
  </div>
</div>

